				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Velocity spell is the 1st thing you'll want to get. 
<br />

<br />
With Velocity, he will soon catch up to you when you do stop in a zone. 
<br />

<br />
The other thing to note, when you zone the pet is automatically right next to you on the other side.  So crossing large distances really isn't a big issue, because the pet will be there on the other side of each zone.   Unlike my group members who sometimes fall 1-2 zones back when I use my horse <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #FF0000"><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal">Lord Zacatac Soulwanderer</a></span></span></span>
