			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Horse medding hasn't been changed in anyway.  The only way you lose the benefit of medding on a horse is if:
<br />

<br />
1- the horse is moving (turning in circles does NOT count as moving)
<br />
2- meleeing while mounted
<br />

<br />
Other than that, you can cast spells, send your pet in, etc all while getting the benefit of sitting down mana regen rates.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=653282" target=_blank>Casala</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1023548" target=_blank>Aderyn</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.hneguild.com" target=_blank>Heaven and Earth</a>, Saryrn
<br />
SOE Magician Class Correspondent</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
